# CDP Platform Rules

Read [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) before cross-service work.

## Architecture

- **Two APIs, one router:** Scraper (`scrapers/`) and StokAPI (`muvstok-api/`) are independent; `cdp_router` coordinates them.
- **No shared Python** between services.
- **Callbacks only** connect workers to n8n (`scraper-result`, `muvstok-result`).

## Agent tiers

| Tier | Entry |
|------|--------|
| Platform | `.agent/index.md` |
| Scraper | `scrapers/AGENTS.md` |
| StokAPI | `muvstok-api/AGENTS.md` |

## n8n

- Edit router Code in `n8n/src/` only; run `make sync-n8n` only with user approval.
- Never use Execute Workflow for StokAPI dispatch.

## Safety

- Never commit secrets, API keys, or webhook HMAC values.
- Never revert user changes without asking.
- Preserve working API contracts when refactoring.
